          "payload": {},
          "sequence": 55,
          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I've successfully completed the fault localization task. Here's a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Fault Localization Summary\n\n**Buggy File**: `sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c`\n\n**Buggy Function**: `azx_resume()` (starting at line 2539)\n\n**Root Cause**: Missing `synchronize_irq()` call after IRQ acquisition during resume\n\n### Detailed Analysis\n\nThe HDA Intel sound driver's resume function has a critical bug that appears as a regression in kernel 3.7.x:\n\n1. **The Problem**:\n   - After suspend to RAM, the sound card stops working properly\n   - Audio becomes choppy with 2-second silences and clicks\n   - Error messages show `azx_get_response` timeouts\n   - The driver falls back to polling mode, disables MSI, and eventually switches to single_cmd mode\n\n2. **Root Cause**:\n   - The `azx_resume()` function (line 2557) calls `azx_acquire_irq()` but **NEVER** calls `synchronize_irq()` afterward\n   - Compare with the probe path (lines 3155-3159) which DOES include `synchronize_irq()`:\n     ```\n     azx_acquire_irq() \u2192 pci_set_master() \u2192 synchronize_irq()  [PROBE]\n     azx_acquire_irq() \u2192 azx_init_pci() \u2192 azx_init_chip()      [RESUME - Missing sync!]\n     ```\n\n3. **Why This Causes Failures**:\n   - When waking from suspend, leftover/pending IRQs from before sleep remain in the IRQ state\n   - Without `synchronize_irq()`, these pending interrupts are never flushed\n   - The codec communication mechanism relies on IRQ handlers\n   - The stale IRQ state prevents proper codec communication\n   - This triggers the exact error cascade: polling fallback \u2192 MSI disable \u2192 single_cmd mode\n\n### Evidence\n- Probe function uses `synchronize_irq()` after IRQ acquisition (line 3159)\n- Resume function is missing this critical synchronization step\n- The bug is a regression that appeared between 3.6.11 (working) and 3.7.1+ (broken)\n- The error messages match perfectly with the timeout handling code path in `azx_get_response()`\n\nThe fault localization result has been written to `/workspace/fault_localization_result.json` with high confidence (0.95).",
